*HR1541*
Introduced Version
HOUSE
RESOLUTION No. ___
Introduced by: Lehman
____________________________________
1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION honoring Representative
2 Edward D. Clere.
3 Whereas, Representative Edward D. Clere, who was first
4 elected to represent the people of House District 72 in 2008,
5 will conclude his legislative service at the end of his current
6 term;
7 Whereas, Representative Clere has served nine consecutive
8 terms in the Indiana House of Representatives. During this
9 time, he has served honorably on several standing committees,
10 including the Education Committee; the Small Business and
11 Economic Development Committee; the Ways and Means
12 Committee, of which he has chaired the Health and Medicaid
13 Subcommittee since 2020; the Public Policy Committee; the
14 Public Health Committee, which he chaired from 2012 to 2015;
15 the Judiciary Committee; and the Financial Institutions
20262412
HR 1541/DI 140 2026

2
1 Committee;
2 Whereas, During his time in office, Representative Clere has
3 focused on health and human services, education, and fiscal
4 policy. He was a leading advocate for Medicaid expansion
5 under the Affordable Care Act, and he is a recognized expert on
6 Medicaid.
7 Whereas, Representative Clere has been a fierce champion
8 for vulnerable and marginalized Hoosiers, including children,
9 seniors, people with disabilities, the economically
10 disadvantaged, LGBTQ+ people, and other minorities;
11 Whereas, Representative Clere has been an outspoken and
12 tireless champion of harm reduction. In response to the 2015
13 HIV outbreak in Scott County, while chairman of the House
14 Public Health Committee, he authored the legislation that
15 allowed communities to provide syringe service programs,
16 which reduce the spread of infection and connect people to
17 recovery and other resources, and these programs have saved
18 and improved countless lives and made communities
19 throughout Indiana safer and stronger;
20 Whereas, Throughout his tenure, Representative Clere has
21 worked to increase legislative engagement and make the
22 legislature more understandable and accessible to his
23 constituents and other Hoosiers. Since 2014, Representative
24 Clere has worked with Dr. Sharron Crowder of the Indiana
25 University School of Nursing to offer a legislative fellowship
26 for graduate nursing students, increasing the voice of the
27 nursing profession in the legislative process;
28 Whereas, In 2019, Representative Clere authored legislation
29 that made Indiana part of the Nurse Licensure Compact,
30 allowing nurses to be licensed in their home state and to
31 practice in other compact member states without obtaining a
32 separate license. The compact has benefited employers, nurses,
33 and patients throughout Indiana, including in Southern
34 Indiana, where it has supported regionalism, a goal
35 Representative Clere has promoted throughout his time in
36 office;
20262412
HR 1541/DI 140 2026

3
1 Whereas, As part of his efforts to support small and
2 independent businesses, Representative Clere has worked
3 extensively on legislation to support and promote the craft
4 alcohol industry, including farm wineries and breweries. He
5 authored the 2013 legislation that created the artisan distiller's
6 permit, giving rise to a major new Hoosier industry;
7 Whereas, Representative Clere has received more than three
8 dozen awards for his legislative service and accomplishments;
9 Whereas, Representative Clere serves on a number of state
10 and local bodies, including the board of Indiana's CHOICE
11 Program, which helps seniors and people with disabilities live
12 independently; the board of the Indiana School for the Deaf;
13 the state's Medicaid Advisory Committee; and the coordinating
14 council for First Steps, Indiana's early-intervention program
15 for infants and toddlers with developmental delays;
16 Whereas, Representative Clere also serves on the boards of
17 the Indiana Minority Health Coalition and the Cardinal Ritter
18 Birthplace Foundation. He is a member of the advisory council
19 of his area agency on aging, LifeSpan Resources, and he
20 co-chairs the Indiana Skills2Compete Coalition;
21 Whereas, Representative Clere has been active in
22 nonpartisan state government organizations, including the
23 Council of State Governments (CSG). He is a former co-chair
24 of CSG's Health Public Policy Committee. He is a 2010
25 graduate of CSG Midwest's Bowhay Institute for Legislative
26 Leadership Development and a former co-chair of the
27 institute's steering committee, on which he continues to serve.
28 He is the second vice chair of the CSG Midwestern Legislative
29 Conference and a longtime member of its executive committee;
30 Whereas, Representative Clere earned a bachelor's degree
31 in sociology from Indiana University Southeast and is a
32 graduate of Leadership Southern Indiana;
33 Whereas, Representative Clere has worked as a Realtor
34 since 2001 and is very involved in historic preservation. He is
35 a former member of the board of Indiana's statewide historic
36 preservation organization, Indiana Landmarks, and he has
20262412
HR 1541/DI 140 2026

4
1 served on the organization's Real Estate Committee for more
2 than 20 years. As a Realtor, he has earned the GRI, CRS, and
3 ABR designations and has served on the board of the Southern
4 Indiana Realtors Association; and
5 Whereas, Representative Clere has enjoyed the unwavering
6 support of his wife, Amy, without whom his service would not
7 have been possible, and their five children, Alan, Lauren,
8 Megan, Madeline, and Hannah: Therefore,
9 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
10 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
11 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
12 honors Representative Edward D. Clere upon his retirement.
13 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
14 Representatives shall transmit a copy of this resolution to
15 Representative Edward D. Clere.
